headline: Candy Kittens owner to Graze on Unilever snack brand
summary: The owner of Candy Kittens, the vegetarian sweet brand, is in talks about a cut-price deal to buy Graze, the snacks range owned by FTSE-100 consumer goods giant Unilever.  Sky News has learnt that Katjes Group, which is headquartered in Germany, is in advanced talks to buy Graze for about £35m.  The price represents a huge discount on the roughly £150m Unilever paid to buy the healthy snacks brand in 2019.
